<TITLE> BNP leader Nazrul Islam Khan hospitalised </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 6 (bdnews24.com)  BNP joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan was admitted to the capital's Heart Foundation after suffering a heart attack early Saturday, his son said. "My father is being kept at the intensive care unit. We request the party leaders and supporters to pray for his recovery," Anik Islam Khan told bdnews24.com. A seven-member medical board has been formed led by cardiology specialist Dr MA Malek. "Nazrul is suffering from heart disease. Nothing certain can be said just now," MA Malek told bdnews24.com. "We will not be able to say that he is out of danger before 48 hours are up," he said. bdnew
